          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Prompt gamma-ray emission in the spontaneous ternary",
                "fission of 252Cf"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N.N.Ajitanand"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "3INDTRM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,NP/A,133,625,1969",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,NP/A,133,625,1969",
                    "doi": "10.1016/0375-9474(69)90561-2",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "NP/A",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "133",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "625"
                      },
                      "date": 1969
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The source of 252Cf deposited over an area of 0.2 cm",
                "diameter on a 61.4 mg/cm2 thick platinum backing. The",
                "source foil was mounted between two steel rings. The",
                "source side was covered by a thin 20 mu-g/cm2 thick",
                "VYNS plastic film to prevent escape of californium",
                "atoms from the platinum foil. The distance between",
                "the source and the surface of the solid-state",
                "detector was l.1 cm. The distance from source to NaI",
                "crystal face was 6.5 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 5 cm x 5 cm NaI(Tl) crystal was used to",
                "detect the gamma rays."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A silicon surface-barrier semiconductor",
                "detector was reverse-biased to a voltage of 90 V to",
                "give a depletion depth of about 310 mu-m for",
                "detection of the fission fragments in the binary",
                "experiment, while in the separate ternary experiment,",
                "it was covered with a 10 mg/cm2 thick aluminium foil",
                "so that only those long-range alpha particles which",
                "had an energy greater than 6.8 MeV could be detected."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measured prompt gammas and fission fragments",
                "in coincidence"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Subtraction of chance coincidences as well as",
                "correction for contributions from fission neutrons",
                "were done. These were calculated to be 8% for the",
                "binary case and 4% for the ternary case."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Digitization is done on Fig.2 in which the X-axis is",
                "given in channel number. Authors also provided the",
                "corresponding gamma energies for each tick. However,",
                "the plot of channel number versus gamma energy is not",
                "linear which may introduce some error."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
